name: Into The Badlands 01
description:
Turn the clock back 30 million years and you would find prehistoric horses, camels, tortoises, pigs, and even rhinoceroses roaming here. The current of this shallow river carried volcanic debris that, layer by layer, formed the rocks seen today. Over time water and wind sculpted the rock into badlands. 

Toadstool Geologic Park, Nebraska
Apple iPhone SE (2nd generation)
